					<p>Land division and individual entitlements have brought an end to the traditional community-managed open rangeland in much of the arid and semi-arid areas of East Africa. But the Olkiramatian Group Ranch in southern Kenya - with a population of about 10,000 - is attracting increasing interest from pastoralists and conservationists alike (Source: The New Agriculturist, November 2008).</p>
