					<p>At a recent conference held in Mombasa, Kenya, delegates from across the banana sector in Africa, gathered to discuss ways in which banana research may be strengthened and banana production transformed across the continent, from a donor-supported system to one driven by the private sector. The New Agriculturist posed some question to conference participants for the November edition of Points of view (Source: The New Agriculturist, November edition, 2008). </p>
