					<p>Before the emergence of a global food-price crisis, African leaders pledged to increase support for agriculture. Recognizing the importance of a strong agricultural sector for economic growth and poverty reduction, they made a commitment to invest 10 percent of their national budgets in agriculture by 2008. As 2008 comes to an end, where do things stand? (Source: IFPRI Forum, October 2008)</p>
