						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Farmers-get-better-yields-from-new-drought-tolerant-cassava" title="Farmers get better yields from new drought-tolerant cassava " alt="link">Farmers get better yields from new drought-tolerant cassava </a></h2>

	
					<p>Dubbed TMS92/0067, the new variety developed by the International Institute for Tropical Agriculture (IITA) produces an average of 30 to 50 tonnes of cassava per hectare as opposed to the 5 tonnes per hectare from local varieties used by farmers in these areas. Beginning 2009, IITA and the International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD) will be distributing the improved variety to 3000 cassava farmers in the Benin Republic, a move aimed at increasing cassava production in that country (Source: Africa Science News Service, 02 November 2008).</p>
