					<p>Kenyan scientists have called on the government to strengthen the existing policy and regulatory environment to boost research on maize varieties that are more disease and pest tolerant. Efforts to tackle underlying threats to maize production in Kenya that includes dangerous pests and diseases have gained momentum as evidenced by scientists while reviewing the end of Phase one and two of Insect Resistant Maize for Africa (IRMA) project in Nairobi last week (Source: Naftali Mwaura, Africa Science News Service, 31 October 2008).</p>
