					<p>National Coordinator of New Partnership for African Development (NEPAD), Ambassador Tunji Olagbunji, has described agriculture and food security as top priority issues of the programme in Africa. African countries have agreed at the AU level to adopt the principles of improving agriculture delivery, rural infrastructure, irrigation food growth and the promotion of rice, cassava farming which can deliver member countries from the menace of poverty and hunger (Source: Seriki Adinoyi, This Day, 28 October 2008).</p>
