<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/African-farmers-set-to-go-bananas" title="African farmers set to go bananas" alt="link">African farmers set to go bananas</a></h2>

	
					<p>The 2008 Banana conference, held in Mombassa this summer came up with a draft 10-year research and development plan that will focus not just on export markets, but also on identifying and pursuing opportunities for Africa's banana growers to gain both higher incomes and greater food security from their crop. The plan addresses themes such as farmers' co-operatives by organising them so they can sell directly to wholesalers, bypassing the middlemen who are costing them millions of shillings in lost income yearly (Source: Catherine Riungu, The East African, 26 October 2008).</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2008</span></p>
