						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/The-small-farmers-arable-farming-revolution" title="The small farmers arable farming revolution" alt="link">The small farmers arable farming revolution</a></h2>

	
					<p>The new arable farming scheme wants to radically change the face of arable farming in Botswana. Row planting will be the new order of the day. The objective is to ensure that farming is carried out scientifically. The new arable farming scheme will also see government digging or acquiring boreholes for the farmers to enable them to practice arable farming even in the dry season. However, the traditional farmer must be involved in the proposed group fencing of the fields (Source: Monkagedi Gaotlhobogwe, Mmegi/The Reporter, 24 October 2008).</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2008</span></p>
